## 5. Color + ANSI

### 5.1. Detection

```python
use_color = (
    "NO_COLOR" not in os.environ      # https://no-color.org/
    and sys.stdout.isatty()           # output to terminal
    and os.environ.get("TERM") != "dumb"
)

# Override через --color
# --color=auto (default, detect) / always / never
```

### 5.2. Semantic colors

| Семантика | Color |
|---|---|
| Error | Red (bold) |
| Warning | Yellow |
| Success | Green |
| Info | Cyan / Blue |
| Header / emphasis | Bold |
| Dim / secondary | Faint / Bright black |

### 5.3. `NO_COLOR` standard

`NO_COLOR=1` env — disable ALL color output. Universal convention ([no-color.org](https://no-color.org)).

### 5.4. Color НЕ единственный носитель информации

`ERROR: ...` prefix + red — два signal'а. Только red — fails при `--no-color` или для colorblind users.

