## 6. Help / documentation

### 6.1. `--help` output structure

```
USAGE:
    mytool [SUBCOMMAND] [OPTIONS] [ARGS]

DESCRIPTION:
    One-paragraph что tool делает.

SUBCOMMANDS:
    create    Create a new X
    list      List existing X
    delete    Delete an X

OPTIONS:
    -v, --verbose       Increase verbosity
    -h, --help          Show this help
        --version       Show version

EXAMPLES:
    mytool create foo
    mytool list --format=json
    mytool delete foo --yes

For more details: mytool <subcommand> --help
```

### 6.2. Examples в help — обязательны

Examples — most useful часть help'а. Real, useful, copy-paste-ready commands.

### 6.3. Man pages

Для serious CLI tools — man pages:

```sh
man mytool          # general
man mytool-create   # subcommand
```

Generated через clap / typer / cobra и проч.

### 6.4. Shell completions

Generate completions для bash / zsh / fish:

```sh
mytool completions bash > /etc/bash_completion.d/mytool
mytool completions zsh > ~/.zsh/completions/_mytool
```

Frameworks (clap / cobra / typer) делают это free.

